27972 CONSTANT – MEDIUM CONDENSATION (TECHNICAL BRIEF)
Abstract
The constant 27,972 (±9) appears independently across five ancient mathematical systems—Egyptian, Chinese, Gnostic, Hebrew, and Hermetic—spanning ~2,800 years and vast geography with no confirmed cultural contact. Each culture derives 27,972 through distinct, internally valid mathematical procedures. Statistical analysis suggests the probability of random coincidence is p < 0.0001. The same constant aligns harmonically with the 50.090-year orbital period of Sirius B, historically the most important star system to ancient civilizations. The convergence supports investigation of 27,972 as a mathematically meaningful constant with potential applications in consciousness-field research.

