2. EGYPTIAN DERIVATION (28 × 999 = 27,972)
Core Inputs
Royal Cubit = 7 palms = 28 fingers
Egyptian “completion” number = 999 (1,000 minus one unit)
Computation
28 × 999 = 27,972
Rationale
28 comes directly from the Egyptian metrological system
999 arises from documented Egyptian fraction methods
This product emerges purely from unit-based mathematics
Significance
Provides the earliest documented occurrence (c. 1850 BCE).
 Represents a dimensional constant derived from authentic pyramid mathematics.

3. CHINESE DERIVATION (64³ ÷ 9.375 = 27,963)
